edu.ucla.sspace.util

Class SparseHashArray<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ucla.sspace.util.SparseHashArray<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SparseArray<T>, Serializable, Iterable<ObjectEntry<T>>

    public class SparseHashArray<T>
extends Object
implements SparseArray<T>, Iterable<ObjectEntry<T>>, Serializable
    A sparse array backed by a HashMap. This class offers amortized constant time access to array indices at the expense of space.

    Instance offer a space savings of retaining only the non-zero indices and values. For large array with only a few values set, this offers a huge savings. However, as the cardinality of the array grows in relation to its size, a dense array will offer better performance in both space and time. This is especially true if the sparse array instance approaches a cardinality to size ratio of .5.

    This class offers much better performance than IntegerMap, but will use significantly more space as the cardinality increases. In addition, this class will marshall primitive types into their reified object forms.

    See Also:
    SparseArray, IntegerMap, Serialized Form
